From the documentation and gleaning at the implementation, it seems like the Stream `onConnectivityChanged` in the `connectivity` package should only emit notifications to changes in the connectivity state. However, when used in a `StreamBuilder`, the stream immediately emits a current connectivity state. What is the reason for this?

The behaviour can be reproduced with the small app below. 

```dart
import 'package:connectivity/connectivity.dart';
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() => runApp(MyApp());

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'connectivity demo',
      home: MyHomePage(),
    );
  }
}

class MyHomePage extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return StreamBuilder<ConnectivityResult>(
      stream: Connectivity().onConnectivityChanged,
      builder:
          (BuildContext context, AsyncSnapshot<ConnectivityResult> snapshot) {
        if (snapshot.hasError) {
          return Text(
              "Something has gone wrong determining the connectivity state");
        }

        if (!snapshot.hasData) {
          return Text("Determining the connectivity state");
        }

        if (snapshot.data == ConnectivityResult.none) {
          return Text("Connectivity lost");
        }

        return Text("OK");
      },
    );
  }
}
```

