Switching tabs in a CupertinoTabScaffold causes ALL of the tabs to be rebuilt, as the `tabBuilder` function is being called by the `_TabSwitchingViewState` at every tab index change.

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Have an app using a CupertinoTabScaffold inside a CupertinoApp
2. Switch between any tab available
3. All tabs (that have been already opened at least once) will be rebuilt

## Solution proposal

What happens, is the condition for rebuilding a tab, will almost always be true (tab_scaffold.dart@338):

```
if (active || tabs[index] != null) {
     tabs[index] = widget.tabBuilder(context, index);
}
```

This can be easily solved by making sure the tab is only rebuilt `if active, and not already cached`

```
if (active && tabs[index] == null) {
     tabs[index] = widget.tabBuilder(context, index);
}
```


